   "source": [
    "netflix%>%\n",
    "drop_na(country)%>%\n",
    "separate(col = country, \n",
    "         sep = ',', \n",
    "         into = \"country_1\", \n",
    "         extra = \"drop\", \n",
    "         remove = F)%>%\n",
    "filter(country_1 == \"United States\"| \n",
    "       country_1 == \"India\"| \n",
    "       country_1 == \"United Kingdom\")%>%\n",
    "group_by(country_1, type)%>%\n",
    "count()%>%\n",
    "ggplot(aes(x= reorder(country_1, n), y = n, fill = type))+\n",
    "geom_col(position = position_dodge())+\n",
    "geom_text(aes(label = n), position = position_dodge(0.9))+   # get labels at center\n",
    "theme_minimal()+\n",
    "labs(title = \"Movies and TV Shows in Top Three Producing Countries \",\n",
    "caption = \"Data Source: Kaggle\",\n",
    "    x = \"Countries\",\n",
    "    y = \"Count\")\n",
    "                  "
   ]

   "source": [
    "netflix %>%\n",
    " filter(release_year != 2021) %>%\n",
    " group_by(type, release_year) %>%\n",
    " count() %>%\n",
    " ggplot() + geom_line(aes(x = release_year, y = n, group = type, color = type)) +\n",
    "  labs(title = 'Trend of titles every year',\n",
    "       subtitle = 'by Content Type',\n",
    "     caption = 'Data Source: Kaggle', \n",
    "      x = \"Release Year\",\n",
    "      y = \"Count\") +\n",
    "theme_minimal()"
   ]

    "netflix %>%\n",
    " select(listed_in) %>%\n",
    " mutate(listed_in = str_split(listed_in,',')) %>%\n",
    " unnest(listed_in) %>%\n",
    " group_by(listed_in) %>%\n",
    " count() %>%\n",
    " arrange(desc(n)) %>%\n",
    " head(20) %>%\n",
    " ggplot(aes(y = reorder(listed_in,n), x = n)) + \n",
    " geom_col() +\n",
    " geom_label(aes(label = n))+\n",
    " labs(title = 'Genre of Shows/Movies',\n",

    "     x = 'Count',\n",
    "     y = 'Theme / Genre') +\n",
    "theme_minimal()"
